This paper deals with facial alignment, which is a computer vision problem related to image processing and analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel approach using a 3D Spatial Transformer Network, which involves modeling camera projection matrices and warping parameters of a 3D model. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the development of algorithms and models for learning from data. The paper also involves the use of a generic 3D model and a Thin Plate Spline (TPS) warping function, which suggests that it may be relevant to the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics). The paper also mentions the use of synthetic data from the 300W-LP dataset, which suggests that it may be relevant to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with facial alignment, which is a problem related to human-computer interaction, suggesting that it may also be relevant to the sub-category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
